Preparation
• Stretch your legs, hips, and lower back before starting.
• Find a clear space where you can lie flat on your back comfortably.
• Lie down with your legs extended straight and your arms at your sides.
• After pressing START, there’s a 4-second countdown before the challenge begins.
During the Challenge
• Keep your legs straight and lift them up toward the ceiling, squeezing your core and legs as you raise them.
• Slowly lower your legs back down, but don’t let them touch the floor—keep tension in your core.
• Continue raising and lowering your legs, maintaining a controlled and steady pace.
• Focus on using your abdominal muscles to control the movement.
Finishing the Challenge
• After 1 minute, you’ll automatically be returned to the homepage.
Exercise Guide
• Start by lying on your back with your legs straight and arms at your sides.
• Engage your core and lift both legs off the ground, keeping them straight.
• Raise your legs as high as you can, then slowly lower them back down without letting them touch the floor.
• Keep a steady, controlled pace throughout the exercise.
• Focus on squeezing your core as you lift and lower your legs to maximize effectiveness.
Note
Push yourself to maintain a steady pace throughout the 1 minute challenge. Keeping your legs straight and controlling each movement will activate your core muscles and help improve lower body strength.
"Every rep brings you closer to your goals. Stay strong!"
